task.summary: Default task
work toward issue #239 - put in unit tests for MuseScore API class

work toward issue #239 - changed issue #238: all apis must implement just a search function, and optionally searchForExactMatch. Changed because MuseScore automatically does searchForAnyMatch in it's api so I'm guessing others will too. - implemented search and searchForExactMatch in museScore API class. Not sure how to get downloadFile working, awaiting response from email.

issue fix #239 - implemented download method and confirmed it works: xml files will have to be unzipped and then parsed at the next stage - added param to download (type) which allows us to use the same method for downloading PDF files, mp3 files etc. which is useful

implemented apimanager - implemented api manager methods and tests - moved api key for mscore into a separate text file which is not on git: will find a way to handle this properly later - issue fix #240

implemented apimanager - implemented api manager methods and tests - moved api key for mscore into a separate text file which is not on git: will find a way to handle this properly later - issue fix #240

implemented ApiManager in musicManager - work on issue #255 - implemented unzipping on download of all api collected files - implemented parsing: yet to implement grabbing the ignored tags from the api data - sub classed MetaParser into OnlineMetaParser, which sets up the source pair and also implements ignoring certain tags - issue fix #243

implemented ApiManager in musicManager - work on issue #255 - implemented grabbing title/composer/lyricist from api layer rather than in parser - yet to implement adding the data to the DB, but have implemented extra bool in query methods to make way for this change

implementing online and offline querying - issue #258 - implemented bool in all methods - implemented a bunch of tests to confirm online and offline functionality - reorganised data layer tests into several classes and left a comment at the top of the test file explaining each one
further online and offline tests - issue #258 - some more tests - ran autopep8 on test files: cleans them all up and makes them fit pep8 standards
further pep8 cleanups - applied autopep8 to classes in ExtractMetadata
further pep8 cleanups - applied autopep8 to classes in ExtractMetadata
further cleanup - applied autopep8 to drawing classes - reorganised gui folder so designer files aren't in the main folder

datalayer integration - integrated online attrib on all methods where relevant - cleaned up drawing files so they now all are to pep8 standard (excluding some camel case problems possibly) - issue fix #258 with 2 new unit tests for every method implementing the online attribute
music manager querying online sources integration - added online param - implemented in each data layer query call - issue fix #259
issue fix #262
issue fix #261 - added tests to check data downloads fine/parses/gets put in db/is cleaned up properly - implemented adding data from api to data layer
issue fix #263 - implemented adding data from API including check to make sure data hasn't been parsed already - implemented searching

issue fix #260: downloading from APIs - implemented download on click as well as deletion from relevant sources table. - implemented temporary license popup: issue #264 - added 2 extra tables (license and secret) to store data for downloading files

issue fix #264: license popup - implemented license popup - implemented loading the license from files - implemented theming and scrolling on text in dark theme: need to apply the same in light theme potentially

work on issue #266 and issue #267 - implemented downloads on a thread: need to implement some kind of loading gif to show whilst this is happening, tho it's relatively quick. issue #267 - implemented querying on a thread: this doesn't quite work yet. Added 2 classes for async tasks, 1 of which uses a queue to pass back data and the other of which doesn't need to. work on issue #266
issue fix #266 - handling querying on a thread: not sure this speeds things up a lot but it looks a lot better now, but need to do a loading gif of some sort potentially
issue fix #203 - rendering now done on a thread and is reasonably quick

more commenting
commenting to several async methods and handlers to explain what they do and when they're executed.

threaded loading proceedure - threaded the main window's loading procedure for the scorebook, auto playlist and personal playlist widgets - yet to implement threading for the db refresh and for the api refresh - work on issue #269
threaded loading proceedure - threading for db procedure and api update - issue fix #269

threaded querying and rendering - using qthread on renderer - still using regular threads on querying so that it's completely realtime: I still don't think this is the right way to achieve this so before open sourcing should look at this bit again. Creating a temporary table and using a model view might be an idea. - issue #270
issue fix #268 not entirely sure on the problem but deleting the db and starting over fixed it for some reason
added 2 more themes - included them in the user guide - retypesetted the fyp - added conclusion which is now up for review with helen

added some templates - changes to background.tex are probably minimal final changes I did when I was tired right before handing in fully. - added a mac bash script template for running lilypond from commandline - added windows bat script template: work on issue #281

work on scripts
- moved all scripts to the scripts folder inside primaries: setup.py needs updating - created python script inside this folder which figures out which OS you're using and then renames the relevant file and gives it permissions - altered main.py so that it gives lilypondrenderer a path to where these scripts lie

setup script adjustments
- adjusted mac setup script so that it creates a whole new file rather than renaming or modifying the old one - created lilypond not found exception and implemented it

setup popup window - work on issue #281 - made a new messagebox class which could be used for generic needs - added a setup window class which handles refresh or browse depending on whether user has a custom install or a basic install of lilypond. This will only show up if the default install is not found, in which case the program will automatically create the new lilypond script in implementation/primaries/scripts (tested and this works fine)

setup popup window - work on issue #281 - changed paths used in setup to be relative - added app.json which is for the node appdmg maker, not working currently - made some changes to setup.py based on new packages. created dmg/app files still crash

windows fixes
- modified setup lilypond script so that it uses the correct windows dir - adjusted bat file location so that it's relative - keys bit has moved and paths for connecting to it are now relative - added if statement around poppler import: temporary fix for windows not having poppler (it does, I just can't find the binary)

lots of test fixes
a bunch of the unit tests were broken because of changes or deprecations of methods. Done the bulk of the data-based tests which failed
A butt load of test fixes

work on issue #237
- there is still a duplication issue having checked with sqlitebrowser. I'm not sure why this is happening - partial temporary fix to the problem by using sets rather than lists: this makes sure that when the query comes back any duplicate entries are ignored

MusicManager test fixes
- work toward issue #237: tests in music manager now pass, but we should look at the underlying problem which is that when data is added for some reason there are duplicates. - replaced files which were accidentally removed in the last commit
more test fixes. Not much to report.

- issue fix #303 ! all global variables are kaboom from MxmlParser. They are all now stored in a dictionary which is held inside the parser class. Helps with testing because now tests can never affect each other, as each one passes in their own copy of the data dictionary.
